Package account

Provides the classes necessary to manage different types of accounts for a user.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Account
    Abstract class representing a user's bank account.
    Asset
    Asset is a child of Account and is an abstract class for all asset accounts: Chequing, Savings, and StockAccount.
    Chequing
    Chequing is a child class of Asset and represents a user's chequing account.
    CreditCard
    CreditCard is a child class of the Debt class.
    Debt
    Debt class is a subclass of the Account.type and the abstract parent class for: CreditCard, and LOC.
    LOC
    A child class of Debt represents a user's line of credit account.
    ReadAndWrite
    This class is used to read and write text files related to accounts.
    Savings
    A child class of Asset represents a user's savings account.
    StockAccount
    This class represents a stock account used for investment activities.

Package account Description

Provides the classes necessary to manage different types of accounts for a user.

Account is the parent class of the rest of the classes in this package.
